50|$|The notorious case of Graham Young, {{which led}} to the Butler Report 1975, led to the {{expansion}} in forensic mental health services with the development of regional (now referred to as <b>medium)</b> <b>secure</b> <b>units</b> in most of the health regions in England, and in Wales. Prior to that there had been only the high security hospitals known as Broadmoor, Rampton, and Ashworth.|$|R
